WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.490 --> 00:00:08.260
You look like a fossil.

2
00:00:08.260 --> 00:00:09.140
Huh?

3
00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.900
With your newspaper and reading glasses.

4
00:00:13.490 --> 00:00:16.210
Is that gramps territory?

5
00:00:16.210 --> 00:00:19.020
In this day and age, you can get 
newspapers on your phone.

6
00:00:19.330 --> 00:00:21.770
Switch to a smartphone already.

7
00:00:21.770 --> 00:00:23.190
See?

8
00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:27.650
A smartphone, huh?

9
00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:31.530
You have to use OINE. 
It's messed up that you can't.

10
00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:34.530
Plus, you can check the papers 
and the latest news.

11
00:00:35.650 --> 00:00:39.560
But my phone still works fine.

12
00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:40.290
Huh?

13
00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:43.380
So good.

14
00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:45.980
Wait, what?

15
00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:48.630
That's weird. The screen won't turn on.

16
00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:52.800
What?

17
00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:55.820
I need to get this repaired.

18
00:00:55.820 --> 00:01:00.050
Don't be silly. Nobody these days 
can repair that ancient artifact.

19
00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:02.690
Just give up and go buy a smartphone.

20
00:01:05.210 --> 00:01:05.980
So yum!

21
00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:56.590
So I went and got a smartphone, 
but this is all new to me.

22
00:02:57.760 --> 00:03:01.240
Wait, you can read papers on this.

23
00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.520
How do I do it?

24
00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:06.840
Guess I'll give it a try.

25
00:03:16.570 --> 00:03:18.600
Nope, I don't have the courage.

26
00:03:20.230 --> 00:03:21.280
Huh?

27
00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:23.290
Wait, what?

28
00:03:23.710 --> 00:03:25.580
What is this screen?

29
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:28.280
How do I get back to the previous screen?

30
00:03:45.220 --> 00:03:47.400
Teach you how to use a smartphone?

31
00:03:47.830 --> 00:03:50.690
I didn't even know you 
were still on a flip phone.

32
00:03:50.690 --> 00:03:52.600
Oh, yeah.

33
00:03:55.070 --> 00:03:56.500
That's so you.

34
00:03:56.500 --> 00:03:57.580
So me?

35
00:03:59.070 --> 00:04:01.250
Please, Tayama-sensei!

36
00:04:01.670 --> 00:04:03.640
Sure, I'll teach you.

37
00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:05.580
Really? Thanks!

38
00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:08.030
So, what are you having trouble with?

39
00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:09.210
Well...

40
00:04:09.580 --> 00:04:14.350
Embarrassing as it is to admit, 
I don't even know the basic controls.

41
00:04:19.330 --> 00:04:20.610
Tayama-san?

42
00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:23.100
Basic controls, right.

43
00:04:23.410 --> 00:04:26.880
Okay, I'll teach you the stuff 
that'll come in handy for you.

44
00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:29.100
Please do.

45
00:04:30.590 --> 00:04:32.860
Let's start with the very basics.

46
00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:37.320
I'm sure even you know how to get back 
to the home screen, so let's skip that.

47
00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.600
Actually, I'd appreciate it 
if you could teach me that, too.

48
00:04:46.060 --> 00:04:48.220
Smartphones have swipe inputs.

49
00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:52.330
Touch the button onscreen and then 
fwip to the character you want to input.

50
00:04:52.330 --> 00:04:54.790
Fwip? Okay.

51
00:04:55.390 --> 00:04:57.390
Let's do "ko."

52
00:04:57.390 --> 00:04:58.210
Fwip...

53
00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:00.760
Wait, no!

54
00:05:03.390 --> 00:05:05.510
That's not what I wanted to do!

55
00:05:08.630 --> 00:05:10.670
Wanna try a different input method?

56
00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:12.430
Yes, please.

57
00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:17.780
Oh, right. I'd like to try reading 
the newspaper on my phone.

58
00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:19.580
Yeah, you can.

59
00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:20.350
Really?

60
00:05:20.780 --> 00:05:25.780
First, you need to open the app store 
to install the newspaper's app.

61
00:05:26.430 --> 00:05:29.460
You can probably find it 
on the home screen.

62
00:05:29.460 --> 00:05:33.540
But you'll need to create 
an account to use it.

63
00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:36.550
And once you do, you log in,

64
00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:38.440
and then you install the newspaper's app.

65
00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:41.660
You'll need to create 
an account for that, too.

66
00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:50.890
Never mind. I'll install it for you.

67
00:05:50.890 --> 00:05:52.210
Sorry, and thank you.

68
00:05:57.950 --> 00:06:02.800
You're the best, Tayama-san. I can 
probably use this like my old phone now.

69
00:06:06.690 --> 00:06:10.450
You'll just have to 
get used to it as you go.

70
00:06:10.450 --> 00:06:15.160
And sorry, but could I ask you 
for one more thing?

71
00:06:15.160 --> 00:06:16.210
Mm?

72
00:06:16.730 --> 00:06:19.820
Would it to be possible 
to increase the font size?

73
00:06:20.210 --> 00:06:22.060
Wha...

74
00:06:22.060 --> 00:06:23.470
Huh?

75
00:06:23.770 --> 00:06:27.990
How'd you know that's a thing when 
you're clueless about smartphones?

76
00:06:27.990 --> 00:06:30.680
I mean, I could do that 
on my flip phone, too.

77
00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:37.050
I-Is there a problem?

78
00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:38.660
Well...

79
00:06:40.910 --> 00:06:44.240
Maybe it's a huge pain 
to change that setting?

80
00:06:58.240 --> 00:07:00.890
I don't mind doing that for you...

81
00:07:20.450 --> 00:07:22.800
But you'd better not stop wearing those.

82
00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:25.360
Got it.

83
00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:27.070
Gimme. I'll change the setting.

84
00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:37.040
Oh, yeah, Sasaki-san. 
To celebrate your smartphone debut,

85
00:07:37.460 --> 00:07:39.870
how's about I give you 
Yamada-san's number?

86
00:07:39.870 --> 00:07:41.800
No, no! No, thank you!

87
00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:45.050
Don't do it, Tayama-san.

88
00:07:45.330 --> 00:07:48.100
That's an invasion of privacy. Also...

89
00:07:48.100 --> 00:07:50.080
It's Yamada-san, of all people!

90
00:07:50.080 --> 00:07:50.930
Too late.

91
00:07:51.310 --> 00:07:52.580
I already added it.

92
00:07:56.750 --> 00:07:57.940
How could you...

93
00:07:58.480 --> 00:07:59.840
Tayama-san?

94
00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:03.790
Anyway, I was just kidding.

95
00:08:03.790 --> 00:08:04.960
D'oh!

96
00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:06.700
Okay, all done.

97
00:08:07.610 --> 00:08:08.780
Tayama-san!

98
00:08:08.780 --> 00:08:10.930
Here. Much easier to read now.

99
00:08:10.930 --> 00:08:12.490
Oh, thanks.

100
00:08:12.490 --> 00:08:14.050
Wait, no!

101
00:08:14.050 --> 00:08:15.870
Gosh, how scary.

102
00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:27.310
Hey there, Yamada-chan.

103
00:08:27.310 --> 00:08:29.010
What's up?

104
00:09:15.190 --> 00:09:17.810
Okay, what have we got today?

105
00:09:24.450 --> 00:09:27.510
He had no idea I took a shot.

106
00:09:28.570 --> 00:09:32.570
All right. Time to put another shift in.
